4. That Conscience is something more than merely Science or Knowledge, appears by the form of the word. In English, the word Conscience, (as Mackintosh has remarked,) always suggests a moral judgment, in addition to a mere Consciousness; Conscicnce in French appears often to go no further than this latter meaning.
